}{}$${\rm{MWD}} = \mathop \sum \limits_{i = 1}^n {X_i}{W_i}$$\end{document}MWD=∑i=1nXiWi

The geometric mean diameter (GMD) was calculated using Eq. (2):
(2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$${\rm{GMD}} = {\rm{exp}}\left({{{\mathop \sum \nolimits_{i = 1}^n {W_i}\ln {X_i}} \over {\mathop \sum \nolimits_{i = 1}^n {W_i}}}} \right)$$\end{document}GMD=exp(∑i=1nWilnXi∑i=1nWi)
where i corresponds to each collected fraction, and Xi and Wi refer to the mean diameter and the dry weight of i-size aggregates, respectively.

The fractal dimension (D) was obtained by regression analysis using Eq. (3):
(3)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
