\begin{document}
}{}$${\rm{(}}3 - D{\rm{)l}}g\left( {{{{d_i}} \over {{d_{{\rm{max}}}}}}} \right) = {\rm{l}}g\left[ {{{{W_{\left( {\rm\delta \le {\it d_i}} \right)}}} \over {{W_0}}}} \right]$$\end{document}(3−D)lg(didmax)=lg[W(δ ≤ di)W0]
where di, dmax, W(δ ≤ di), and W0 refer to the average diameter of an i-size aggregate, the maximum diameter of all aggregates tested, the weight of aggregates with particle size < di, and the total weight of aggregates, respectively. Finally, D was obtained by regression analysis.
